{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The evaluate-stage command stores grounding into a dedicated `grounding` artifact, not the `plan` artifact.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is command-to-artifact-store handoff (wrong slot key), not pure algorithm logic. No real OS/network/subprocess is required, and correctness does not depend on model output quality. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because behavior text is about artifact destination (`grounding` vs `plan`), not LLM judgment.","test_description":"Run evaluate-stage command with a real in-process artifact repository (or local test DB) and assert: `grounding` artifact is created/updated, `plan` is unchanged by this stage.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The implement-stage flow reads grounding when available and still writes its execution output to `plan`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module orchestration: read one artifact, write another, preserve role separation. The failure appears at module boundaries (artifact reader + implement writer). Rejected Agentic because behavior text targets routing/handoff (`reads grounding`, `writes ... to plan`) rather than evaluating LLM output quality.","test_description":"Seed run context with a `grounding` artifact, execute implement flow with deterministic model stub, assert implement consumed grounding input and wrote output only to `plan` artifact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Deep-dive no longer overwrites `plan` as a redundant side effect when diagnosis already exists in issue content.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Need to verify deep-dive stage plus artifact-write side effects together