tep emergent failures in handoff and model-mediated use of grounding.","test_description":"Run the real chain end-to-end with live model calls across stages; assert final `plan` content incorporates key grounding facts generated earlier, and trace links confirm same-run propagation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.3,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When grounding is absent, implement falls back safely and still emits a valid plan artifact without corrupting other stored artifacts.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is fallback and data-integrity behavior across implement logic + artifact store. It requires checking absence handling and non-target artifact preservation together. Rejected Agentic because behavior text focuses on safe fallback and artifact integrity, not model output quality.","test_description":"Start run context without `grounding` but with other artifacts present; execute implement flow and assert: a valid `plan` is emitted, no exceptions, and unrelated artifacts remain unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
